example.statement:
For each function below, (1) find the domain of the composite function, (2) completely decompose the function into smaller ones.



		f(x) = \dfrac{1}{x+2}




		q(x) = (2x+1)^5		




		s(h) = \sin \left(5h^2 + \dfrac{1}{h}\right)		




		y(r) = \dfrac{5.317}{(2r^5 + 1.7)^2}		




		g(x) = \tan (x^2)

